Since you are using an external tomcat for deployment by setting the `spring-boot-starter-tomcat` as `provided` **scope**. Try adding the below scope to the jasper:

        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.tomcat.embed&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;tomcat-embed-jasper&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;provided&lt;/scope&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;

The jasper dependency is not included in the embedded tomcat but since the deployment is to an external one , the tomcat will already have this. So you could mark it as provided. The jasper dependency is the one which transpile the jsp.Also ensure that a **war** packaging is used as JSP won&#39;t work properly with **jar** as packaging in spring boot.[Read][1]


  [1]: https://dzone.com/articles/spring-boot-embedded-tomcat-example

